[[File:XC3 Tutorial Elite Monster.jpg|thumb|An Elite Bunnit]] '''Elite Monsters''' are [[Enemy (XC3)|enemies]] in {{XC3}}. They are monsters that are stronger than [[Normal Monster]]s. They can be identified by having blue-colored wing decorations on either side of their level tag. Among generic enemies of the same level and species, they are the second-strongest type of enemy, only beaten by [[Unique Monster (XC3)|Unique Monsters]].
Most Elite monsters are simply stronger versions of enemies of the same species, making them tougher to kill than normal monsters. However, some enemy types only appear as Elite monsters.
When battling an Elite monster, the [[Xenoblade 3 Original Soundtrack|track]] [[:File:Xenoblade_Chronicles_3_%E2%80%93_A_Formidable_Enemy|"A Formidable Enemy"]] will be played over the regular battle theme, unless a Unique Monster is present in the fight.
Defeating an Elite monster yields increased rewards. The following rewards are multiplied when compared to a normal monster: * [[Experience Points (XC3)|EXP]]: 250% of the normal amount * [[Class (XC3)|CP]]: 300% of the normal amount * [[Gold]]: 350% of the normal amount {{clr}}
